trans-unit.source: Module Overview
trans-unit.target: Module Overview

trans-unit.source: You can use the <ui>Create R Model</ui> module to create an untrained model from R script that you provide.
trans-unit.target: You can use the <ui>Create R Model</ui> module to create an untrained model from R script that you provide.

trans-unit.source: You can base your model on any learner that is included in an R package in the Azure Machine Learning environment.
trans-unit.target: You can base your model on any learner that is included in an R package in the Azure Machine Learning environment.

trans-unit.source: After you create the model, you can use <link xlink:href="5cc7053e-aa30-450d-96c0-dae4be720977" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Train Model</link> to train the model on a dataset, like any other learner in Azure Machine Learning.
trans-unit.target: After you create the model, you can use <link xlink:href="5cc7053e-aa30-450d-96c0-dae4be720977" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Train Model</link> to train the model on a dataset, like any other learner in Azure Machine Learning.

trans-unit.source: The trained model can be passed to <link xlink:href="401b4f92-e724-4d5a-be81-d5b0ff9bdb33" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Score Model</link> to use the model to make predictions.
trans-unit.target: The trained model can be passed to <link xlink:href="401b4f92-e724-4d5a-be81-d5b0ff9bdb33" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Score Model</link> to use the model to make predictions.

trans-unit.source: The trained model can then be saved, and the scoring workflow can be published as a web service.
trans-unit.target: The trained model can then be saved, and the scoring workflow can be published as a web service.

trans-unit.source: Currently it is not possible to pass the scored results of an R model to <link xlink:href="927d65ac-3b50-4694-9903-20f6c1672089" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Evaluate Model</link> or <link xlink:href="75fb875d-6b86-4d46-8bcc-74261ade5826" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Cross Validate Model</link>.
trans-unit.target: Currently it is not possible to pass the scored results of an R model to <link xlink:href="927d65ac-3b50-4694-9903-20f6c1672089" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Evaluate Model</link> or <link xlink:href="75fb875d-6b86-4d46-8bcc-74261ade5826" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Cross Validate Model</link>.

trans-unit.source: If you need to evaluate a model, you can write custom R script and run it using the <link xlink:href="30806023-392b-42e0-94d6-6b775a6e0fd5" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Execute R Script</link> module.
trans-unit.target: If you need to evaluate a model, you can write custom R script and run it using the <link xlink:href="30806023-392b-42e0-94d6-6b775a6e0fd5" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Execute R Script</link> module.

trans-unit.source: The following example demonstrates the structure of these scripts and how to implement a model.

trans-unit.source: For this example, we implement a two-class Naïve Bayes classifier by using the <database>e1070</database> package, but you can use any type of learner that is included in the many R packages supported in Azure Machine Learning.
trans-unit.target: For this example, we implement a two-class Naïve Bayes classifier by using the <database>e1070</database> package, but you can use any type of learner that is included in the many R packages supported in Azure Machine Learning.

trans-unit.source: Training Script
trans-unit.target: Training Script

trans-unit.source: The part of the R script that trains the model is run within the <link xlink:href="5cc7053e-aa30-450d-96c0-dae4be720977" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Train Model</link> module.
trans-unit.target: The part of the R script that trains the model is run within the <link xlink:href="5cc7053e-aa30-450d-96c0-dae4be720977" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Train Model</link> module.

trans-unit.source: The following example demonstrates how to load an R package, create model using one of the learners in that package, and configure the feature and label columns using the predefined constants and functions provided in <ui>Create R Model</ui>.
trans-unit.target: The following example demonstrates how to load an R package, create model using one of the learners in that package, and configure the feature and label columns using the predefined constants and functions provided in <ui>Create R Model</ui>.

trans-unit.source: Let’s go through the example script line-by-line.
trans-unit.target: Let’s go through the example script line-by-line.

trans-unit.source: The first line loads the R package, <embeddedLabel>e1071</embeddedLabel>, which contain the Naïve Bayes classifier algorithm we want to use.
trans-unit.target: The first line loads the R package, <embeddedLabel>e1071</embeddedLabel>, which contain the Naïve Bayes classifier algorithm we want to use.

trans-unit.source: Since this is one of the packages pre-installed in the Azure Machine Learning environment, you don’t need to download or install the package.
trans-unit.target: Since this is one of the packages pre-installed in the Azure Machine Learning environment, you don’t need to download or install the package.

trans-unit.source: For information about how to get the full list of supported packages, see <link xlink:href="d42f7c08-039b-4f91-809d-aa138fccf254" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">R Language Modules</link>.
trans-unit.target: For information about how to get the full list of supported packages, see <link xlink:href="d42f7c08-039b-4f91-809d-aa138fccf254" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">R Language Modules</link>.

trans-unit.source: The next three lines get the feature columns and the label column from the dataset, and combine them into a new R data frame that is named <codeInline>train.data</codeInline>:
trans-unit.target: The next three lines get the feature columns and the label column from the dataset, and combine them into a new R data frame that is named <codeInline>train.data</codeInline>:

trans-unit.source: The predefined function, <codeInline>get.label.columns()</codeInline>, returns the column that is selected as the class label in the <link xlink:href="5cc7053e-aa30-450d-96c0-dae4be720977" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Train Model</link> module.
trans-unit.target: The predefined function, <codeInline>get.label.columns()</codeInline>, returns the column that is selected as the class label in the <link xlink:href="5cc7053e-aa30-450d-96c0-dae4be720977" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Train Model</link> module.

trans-unit.source: The predefined function, <codeInline>get.feature.columns()</codeInline>, selects the columns that were designated as features in the metadata for dataset.
trans-unit.target: The predefined function, <codeInline>get.feature.columns()</codeInline>, selects the columns that were designated as features in the metadata for dataset.

trans-unit.source: By default, all columns except the label column are considered features in Studio.
trans-unit.target: By default, all columns except the label column are considered features in Studio.

trans-unit.source: If you want to select specific columns as features, use <link xlink:href="370b6676-c11c-486f-bf73-35349f842a66" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Metadata Editor</link>, or select a set of columns within the R script.
trans-unit.target: If you want to select specific columns as features, use <link xlink:href="370b6676-c11c-486f-bf73-35349f842a66" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Metadata Editor</link>, or select a set of columns within the R script.

trans-unit.source: In the fifth and sixth lines, the predefined function, <codeInline>get.feature.column.names(dataset)</codeInline>, is used to get feature column names from the dataset.
trans-unit.target: In the fifth and sixth lines, the predefined function, <codeInline>get.feature.column.names(dataset)</codeInline>, is used to get feature column names from the dataset.

trans-unit.source: Those names are designated as the names for columns in <codeInline>train.data</codeInline>, and a temporary name <codeInline>Class</codeInline> is created for the label column.
trans-unit.target: Those names are designated as the names for columns in <codeInline>train.data</codeInline>, and a temporary name <codeInline>Class</codeInline> is created for the label column.

trans-unit.source: The final line of the code trains the Naïve Bayes classifier algorithm by using the labels and features in the <codeInline>train.data</codeInline> data frame.
trans-unit.target: The final line of the code trains the Naïve Bayes classifier algorithm by using the labels and features in the <codeInline>train.data</codeInline> data frame.

trans-unit.source: The model must always be assigned to a variable called <codeInline>model</codeInline> in both the train and score scripts.
trans-unit.target: The model must always be assigned to a variable called <codeInline>model</codeInline> in both the train and score scripts.

trans-unit.source: Publishing the R Model as a Web Service
trans-unit.target: Publishing the R Model as a Web Service

trans-unit.source: After you have run the experiment by using the R model, you can publish the experiment as a web service.
trans-unit.target: After you have run the experiment by using the R model, you can publish the experiment as a web service.

trans-unit.source: To publish the experiment
trans-unit.target: To publish the experiment

trans-unit.source: Click <ui>Create Scoring Experiment</ui> in the experiment editor.
trans-unit.target: Click <ui>Create Scoring Experiment</ui> in the experiment editor.

trans-unit.source: The trained R model is saved, and the training experiment graph is transformed into a scoring experiment.
trans-unit.target: The trained R model is saved, and the training experiment graph is transformed into a scoring experiment.

trans-unit.source: Run the scoring experiment at least once.
trans-unit.target: Run the scoring experiment at least once.

trans-unit.source: Click <ui>Publish Web Service</ui>.
trans-unit.target: Click <ui>Publish Web Service</ui>.

trans-unit.source: By default, the web service expects all input columns from the training data to be provided, including the label column.
trans-unit.target: By default, the web service expects all input columns from the training data to be provided, including the label column.

trans-unit.source: You can add an instance of <link xlink:href="1ec722fa-b623-4e26-a44e-a50c6d726223" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Project Columns</link> between the input data source and the <link xlink:href="401b4f92-e724-4d5a-be81-d5b0ff9bdb33" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Score Model</link> module to exclude the label you’re trying to predict.
trans-unit.target: You can add an instance of <link xlink:href="1ec722fa-b623-4e26-a44e-a50c6d726223" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Project Columns</link> between the input data source and the <link xlink:href="401b4f92-e724-4d5a-be81-d5b0ff9bdb33" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Score Model</link> module to exclude the label you’re trying to predict.

trans-unit.source: Technical Notes
trans-unit.target: Technical Notes

trans-unit.source: The model is cached after the first run of the module and the module is not invoked in subsequent runs until any changes in input scripts are done.
